places he encounters along the
way.

52:44.795 --> 52:50.401 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's already logged about 4,000
miles. What's it like? You can
ask him yourself at 1:00

52:50.401 --> 52:54.338 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
p.m. Eastern tomorrow on our
Twitter chat with National
Geographic. Details are on our

52:54.338 --> 52:57.708 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
home page.

52:57.708 --> 53:03.514 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
